modules.description: This module supports constructing and modifying event databases by opening a writeable database, adding events with associated fields, and finalizing or appending to existing databases. It operates on event streams with UUIDs, timestamps, and field values. Concrete use cases include ingesting log data into TrailDB or merging multiple event datasets.

This module provides functions to iterate over and access events in a trail within a TrailDB database. It supports operations to retrieve the next or current event in a trail, get the length of the trail, and navigate through trails using a cursor. Concrete use cases include processing event streams sequentially, analyzing user behavior trails, and extracting specific event data from large datasets.

This module evaluates events against boolean combinations of field-value constraints, using conjunctions and disjunctions of positive or negative field item matches. It works with TrailDB's internal item representations to filter events based on exact field value conditions. Concrete use cases include selecting events where specific fields match or exclude certain values, such as tracking user activity with particular attributes or excluding known patterns from query results.

This module offers operations for constructing and querying structured event data, focusing on efficient traversal and filtering of events based on field constraints. It works with data structures such as events, fields, UUIDs, timestamps, and trail-to-identifier mappings, while supporting error handling for robust data processing. It is suited for use cases like real-time analytics, log processing, or system monitoring where structured event streams require low-latency querying and aggregation.
